Hellraiser IV: Bloodline is a 1996 American horror film and the fourth installment in the Hellraiser series, which serves as both a prequel and a sequel. Directed by Joe Chappelle and Kevin Yagher, the film stars Doug Bradley as Pinhead, reprising his role and now the only remaining original character and cast member. Other cast members include Bruce Ramsay, Valentina Vargas and Kim Myers. It was actor Adam Scott's first film.This was the last Hellraiser film to be released in theaters and the last to have any sort of involvement with series creator Clive Barker and also the final installment in chronology.
